So being on Wichita State University, the whole place is made for their college students, so you may fell out of place, but no one will actually know or care if you aren't a student.

Most of the parking requires a permit, but there's free thirty minute parking by the campus bus stop right near the building.

name: Tallahassee Rock Gym
directions: On the left of the lobby room, right next to the refrigerator where they sell Gatorade and candy!
comment: I'm almost certain you can just ask to use the bathroom and they'll let you. I'm not sure, so check out the place and ask around just to be certain. Also! If you want to go to this gym to work out, I recommend it, as the coaches and people there are extremely accepting. My friend recently came out as non-binary to our team, and everyone immediately switched to their preferred pronouns! I've also recently came out as bisexual to my team, and they don't seem bothered by it. Again, a safe place that I've been going to for three years. I've seen that rock climbing has attracted types of people that could become a closely knit community, which would accept you for who you are. Don't be afraid to go there! Stay safe, everyone!

name: Bartlett Hall
directions: Ground floor, near the stairs and rec room
comment: Access is restricted to students living in Bartlett and their guests.  It is also a disability accessible bathroom

name: Dee-O-Gee
directions: End of the hallway on the left

name: Kohl's
directions: There is a family bathroom all the way to the left when you walk in, in the section with the greeting cards.

name: Mrs. London's
comment: The staff are very kind and helpful. Even if eating at the restaurant next door (Max London's) you can still get to this restroom for use.

name: Mattox Hall

name: Peet's Capital One Cafe
directions: All the way in the back past the Peet's counter
comment: The single stall bathrooms are gender labeled but the staff will let you know that they're unisex. Most staff will just let you go. One or two baristas will require a purchase, but they'll point you toward things that cost less than a dollar, then will give you the code.

name: SoundWaters

name: UNCG School of Music

comment: A sign is up by the door, knock, and then it's the room through the next door. Beware of random people practicing though.

name: The Rose O’Neill Literary House
directions: The lit house is the white house with the large open porch across from the main campus. The bathroom is in the small hallway right next to the kitchen on the ground floor.
comment: Lit house is only accessible on weekdays during the day and early evening. You may get a weird look if you go in and are clearly not a student, but everyone who works and hangs out there is very LGBT friendly.

name: Hawkins Residence Hall
directions: In through the entrance from the street and to the right.
comment: Private residence hall, can't enter the building after 11PM without keycard access.

name: CCBC Essex
directions: There are unisex bathrooms in at least two of the campus buildings; the Mathematics and Sciences Hall on every floor, and in the library at the entrance.
comment: The bathrooms on campus are not blocked to non-students, but in a pinch, it's a bit of a walk to any of the buildings. If you are a student, however, the unisex bathrooms are easy to find and no one will judge you for using them.

name: Washington College Miller Library
directions: Library is in middle of campus, there is signage around to help you find it. The bathroom itself is in the back of the ground floor near the Quantitative Skills center.
comment: Can't be accessed in evenings or on weekends without a student ID. Only public gender neutral restroom on campus as of 2017.

comment: Must be a patient
